last_episode_to_air.name: Episode 24
last_episode_to_air.overview: After 45 days of battling it out in Samoa, the final three will be pushed to their limits. Who will be crowned Sole Survivor in Titans vs Rebels?

name: Australian Survivor
overview: Australian Survivor sees 24 tough and tenacious people marooned on a tropical island with little more than the clothes on their backs and the drive to be the sole survivor. Contestants are deprived of basic comforts and must build their own shelter, light their own fires, gather their own food and fend for themselves.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview:
The season was filmed in Whaler's Way, an Eyre Peninsula coastal nature reserve near Port Lincoln, South Australia in the Great Australian Bight, where numerous ships had sunk off the coast in the past, setting up the season's nautical theme.

The series was filmed in November and December 2001 and aired weekly between February and May 2002 on the Nine Network, culminating in a live finale.

seasons.name: Celebrity Survivor: Vanuatu
seasons.overview: The second season of Australian Survivor, also known as Australian Celebrity Survivor and Celebrity Survivor: Vanuatu, featured 12 Australian celebrity contestants competing on the Vanuatuan island of Éfaté over 25 days for a grand prize of A$100,000 for the winner's chosen charity for the Seven Network.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: This Season was filmed in Samoa from May to July 2016 and premiered on 21 August 2016 on Network Ten.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: The fourth season of Australian Survivor was filmed on the Samoan island of Upolu and featured 24 Australian castaways competing for 55 days in the Samoan jungle for a grand prize of A$500,000.

seasons.name: Champions vs. Contenders I
seasons.overview:
The fifth season of Australian Survivor, also known as Australian Survivor: Champions vs. Contenders.

The season featured 24 contestants divided into two tribes: "Champions", composed of twelve high-achievers who excelled in their fields, and "Contenders", composed of twelve everyday Australians.

seasons.name: Champions vs. Contenders II
seasons.overview:
The sixth season of Australian Survivor, also known as Australian Survivor: Champions vs. Contenders.

As with the previous season, the season features 24 contestants divided into two tribes: "Champions", composed of twelve high-achievers who excelled in their fields, and "Contenders", composed of twelve everyday Australians.

seasons.name: All Stars
seasons.overview:
In Australian Survivor: All Stars, the game’s most iconic Champions and super fans, return for a slice of the scheming pie in the ultimate re-match.

Returning to a game they all think they’ve mastered, the players are in for a rude awakening. The challenges are harder, the alliances stronger and the blindsides more epic.

seasons.name: Brains vs. Brawn
seasons.overview: Australian Survivor sees 24 tough and tenacious people marooned on a tropical island with little more than the clothes on their backs and the drive to be the sole survivor.

seasons.name: Blood vs Water
seasons.overview: Located in Far North Queensland, 24 castaways face off with their loved ones to see who has what it takes to be crowned Sole Survivor.

seasons.name: Heroes vs. Villains
seasons.overview: In the game of Australian Survivor, who does it better? A hero or a villain? This season, we are back to where it all began. Samoa. Where the beautiful beaches will see heroes and villains battle it out in gruelling challenges to come out on top. Hosted by Jonathan LaPaglia, the eighth season of Australian Survivor is an unrelenting test of courage, endurance and strength that will push people to their limits and beyond.

seasons.name: Titans v Rebels
seasons.overview:
In this season, twenty-four contestants were stranded in Samoa and divided into two tribes of Titans and Rebels.

The season was filmed in Upolu, Samoa, the same location of the previous season.

episodes.name: This Game Is Way Different Than It Looks
He's a Threat, She's a Threat, We're All Threats!

1.name: Season 1
1.overview:
The season was filmed in Whaler's Way, an Eyre Peninsula coastal nature reserve near Port Lincoln, South Australia in the Great Australian Bight, where numerous ships had sunk off the coast in the past, setting up the season's nautical theme.

The series was filmed in November and December 2001 and aired weekly between February and May 2002 on the Nine Network, culminating in a live finale.

2.name: Celebrity Survivor: Vanuatu
2.overview: The second season of Australian Survivor, also known as Australian Celebrity Survivor and Celebrity Survivor: Vanuatu, featured 12 Australian celebrity contestants competing on the Vanuatuan island of Éfaté over 25 days for a grand prize of A$100,000 for the winner's chosen charity for the Seven Network.

episodes.name: I Always Wanted to Play the Villain
episodes.overview: Twenty-four Australians arrive on the tropical island of Samoa ready to outwit, outplay and outlast each other in order to win the half a million dollar prize and the title of soul survivor.

episodes.name: Paranoia Will Do Crazy Things To You
episodes.overview: The tribes compete in an Immunity Challenge to avoid tribal council where they will be forced to vote a team mate off the island. Who will be the second contestant to leave the island?

episodes.name: A Little Jaunty Rhyme
episodes.overview: A physical Reward Challenge will push the tribes to their limits for a tarp & cushions. Later, the Immunity Challenge sees the tribes compete on a puzzle to avoid heading to Tribal Council.

episodes.name: A Real Mad Moral Dilemma
episodes.overview: One tribe is struggling to make fire and morale is at an all-time low. They must win today's Immunity Challenge to lift their spirits & avoid Tribal Council to vote another contestant off the island.

episodes.name: Flippity
episodes.overview: Facing elimination, the three tribes head to the Immunity Challenge. Which team will return to camp triumphant and which teams will be left to ponder what happened at Tribal Council?

episodes.name: Welcome To Our Electric Box Of Crayons
episodes.overview: The tribes are still reeling after last night's tribal council but will need to put their differences aside and unite to compete in an epic Immunity Challenge.

episodes.name: Revenge Is On The Cards
episodes.overview: The reward challenge will set tummies rumbling as the contestants compete for a BBQ feast. In the Immunity Challenge each tribe will be challenged to carry their own weight to avoid Tribal Council.

episodes.name: Game Changing Advantage
episodes.overview: Last night's losing tribe is on edge after another tense elimination. One contestant is feeling increasingly insecure about their spot in the tribe. Will they be eliminated next?

episodes.name: Divided
episodes.overview: As the dust settles from last night's shock tribal council result, some tribe mates are feeling anxious about their position in the game and scramble to make new alliances.

episodes.name: I Have A Ferrari In My Brain
episodes.overview: One tribe mate is left feeling guilty and in shock after last night's tribal council. The result has caused a rift in the tribe and a very obvious division between some tribe mates.

episodes.name: The Chicken Debate
episodes.overview: After receiving a vote at tribal council, one tribe member is shocked after surviving the vote. They are hurt and angry, but do they have the numbers to seek revenge?

episodes.name: No Such Thing As A Sure Thing
episodes.overview: Tribal tensional continues to escalate when two people come to blows over their sleeping arrangements. With the losing team heading to tribal council who will be the next person to leave the island?

episodes.name: Disbelief And Relief
episodes.overview: Which tribe can muster the strength to win the reward challenge for a huge traditional Samoan feast? Plus, Jonathan reveals a massive twist that will give a tribe a huge advantage in the game.

episodes.name: Revenge, Redemption, And Justice
episodes.overview: One tribemate wakes the morning after Tribal Council furious that their strategy has been exposed while other tribemates bask in their new found power heading into the Reward & Immunity Challenge.

episodes.name: Sunaapu Surveillance
episodes.overview: One tribe is still shocked after the last tribal council, but they try and rally each other back together anticipating another Immunity Challenge to avoid another elimination.

episodes.name: All Hell Has Broken Loose
episodes.overview: After the final tribe merger the castaways jostle for position to control the game. With power held by a select few one contestant sets upon a plan to change the game but is it too little too late?

episodes.name: A State Of Chaos And Confusion
episodes.overview: One tribe mate is furious after last night's tribal council and is determined to get revenge. At the reward challenge Jonathan announces that the winning team will each receive a letter from home.

episodes.name: Exiled
episodes.overview: Last night's tribal council left alliances exposed and the tribe in turmoil. Paranoia sets in for some tribe mates. Will they have to turn on each other just to keep themselves in the game?

episodes.name: All Guns Blazing
episodes.overview: This reward challenge is for a delicious Sunday Roast which will be perfect fuel for the immunity challenge. Who will be safe from tonight's tribal council vote?

episodes.name: The Game Is On Fire
episodes.overview: Tribal politics continue to escalate but one tribemate thinks their back is against the wall and no amount of scrambling can save them. Will they get a lifeline?

episodes.name: This Is The Door Exploding
episodes.overview: Some tribemates are furious about the accusations made at the last tribal council. Now with the jury there to watch the discussions play out, will it impact their chance of winning?

episodes.name: Don't Mess With Me
episodes.overview: With alliances hanging in the balance, the contestants head to the reward challenge in an effort to win a luxury spa night. Later, who will be voted out and become the next jury member?

episodes.name: The New Alliance
episodes.overview: Emotions are running high now that the castaways are getting closer to the finale. The tribemates are starting to second guess their strategies. Is now the time to change it up?

episodes.name: Two Seconds
episodes.overview: With only five contestants remaining, strategy reaches fever pitch as each tribemate ponders who should be the next to go.

episodes.name: Desperation Is A Stinky Cologne
episodes.overview: Only four contestants remain and the next move they make will determine the finalists. The penultimate Immunity Challenge is one that each tribemate feels confident they can win.

episodes.name: Take It All In
episodes.overview: With only three castaways left remaining, who will win the half a million dollar prize and the title of sole survivor?

3.name: Season 3
3.overview: This Season was filmed in Samoa from May to July 2016 and premiered on 21 August 2016 on Network Ten.

episodes.name: Welcome to Survivor
episodes.overview: 24 Australians arrive on the tropical island of Samoa ready to outwit, outplay and outlast each other in order to win the half a million dollar prize and the title of sole survivor.

episodes.name: The Chicken Idol
episodes.overview: The perfect storm is brewing in Samoa as the tribes fight to protect supplies & maintain fire in adverse conditions. However, how will the prospect of a possible idol at play tamper with the newly formed friendships?

episodes.name: The Other Nail in Her Coffin
episodes.overview: As a major alliance crumbles, one tribe scrambles to avoid elimination. The other tribe grows frustrated with two members and make moves to have them removed next.

episodes.name: Cookie Monster
episodes.overview: Food is the only thing on the minds of the castaways as one member from each camp faces a painful moral dilemma which could have dramatic ramifications for the tribemates & their own game.

episodes.name: Line in the Sand
episodes.overview: Tensions run high as the castaways endure further wind & rain without fire and shelter before a lengthy immunity challenge finishing with the next Tribal Council.

episodes.name: Put Both Their Necks on the Block & Start Chopping
episodes.overview: Blatant lies at the last tribal council has put everyone in one camp on edge. Will they be able to put their differences aside to win the reward challenge or will they leave hungry?

episodes.name: Spontaneous and Bombastic
episodes.overview: A brutal tribal council the night before has left one castaway on the war path seeking retribution. At the immunity challenge, the tribes must take part in a physical Sumo'an contest

episodes.name: At Least I Can Do My Nails
episodes.overview: As both tribes appear to reach their wits end, the prospect of a luxurious and cleansing reward could be enough to keep the castaways in the game for weeks to come.

episodes.name: Yogapants and Sideshow Bob
episodes.overview: Winning immunity has never been so vital to resettling the balance within each tribe, and with a highly competitive challenge that encourages fair contact, things are sure to get feisty.

episodes.name: Opening Up Shop
episodes.overview: Social divisions begin to exhaust castaways as one tribe breaks down ahead of the next immunity challenge. Will they be able to come together to avoid another visit to tribal council?

episodes.name: Deep in the Mangroves
episodes.overview: Aligned castaways find themselves at each other's throats over who is doing enough work around camp, but is one player acting lazy to divide the tribe?

episodes.name: The King of the Jungle
episodes.overview: A surprise challenge sees one castaway return to camp with an unexpected power that could push tensions to breaking point. Later, will one castaway past come back to haunt them at tribal council?

episodes.name: Hanging on the Edge of a Cliff With My Nails
episodes.overview: Alliances continue to flip as a former power player finds themselves at the bottom of their tribe, and a last minute scramble to return to their former glory will turn friend against friend.

episodes.name: Absolute Chaos
episodes.overview: Betrayal runs rampant within both tribes as deceptive immunity clues and relentless strategising begins to place targets on the backs of castaways who had previously flown under the radar.

episodes.name: One Night Stand
episodes.overview: The fallout from one of the most dramatic Tribal Councils this season sends shockwaves through one tribe as castaways scramble to repair broken bonds.

episodes.name: This is Where the War Really Begins
episodes.overview: Change is in the air as time comes for the biggest event in the game so far: a merger. Emotions continue to run high when a particularly difficult reward challenge offers a deeply sentimental prize.

episodes.name: Jamgate
episodes.overview: The fallout from the first group tribal council tears a rift between the newly formed tribe, resulting in a huge clash of alliances. Who will be the next contestant to have their flame extinguished?

episodes.name: The Champagne Alliance
episodes.overview: A shock display of power at the last tribal council places an immediate target on one castaway. Will the new shift in camp dynamics be enough to remove a prolific player from the game?

episodes.name: Desperate Times, Desperate Measures
episodes.overview: A scheming conversation is overheard, putting one contestant in the firing line, and an alliance is shattered, resulting in one of the most divided tribal councils this series.

episodes.name: Survivor Charades
episodes.overview: Another alliance is in jeopardy as one contestant decides to flip on a fellow tribesman, planning the biggest blindside this season, but an unexpected turn of events forces the castaway to reconsider.

episodes.name: Winning Her Over with Some Sweet Lollies
episodes.overview: The battle for individual immunity is at an all-time high and contestants must compete in a fast-paced memory challenge to secure their safety for another day going into tribal council.

episodes.name: Happy Days
episodes.overview: With alliances crumbling and paranoia setting in, all six castaways are determined to win individual immunity. In an explosive Tribal Council, one contestant holds the power, but who will they choose?

episodes.name: Conquered
episodes.overview: After seven weeks on the island of Samoa, only five contestants remain in the race towards winning $500,000 in prize money. Who will become the next member of the Jury?

episodes.name: Day 50
episodes.overview: After 50 testing days on the island of Samoa, the final four contestants go into the challenge, not for immunity but for an advantage: to eliminate a member of the jury at Tribal Council.

episodes.name: Civilized Scrambling
episodes.overview: The final four start to plan and collude on who they will vote off next at Tribal Council, but this is Survivor, and anybody could win immunity.

episodes.name: The Wet, the Cold, the Wind, and the Dark
episodes.overview: With only three castaways remaining, who will win the $500,000 prize and the title of sole survivor?

4.name: Season 4
4.overview: The fourth season of Australian Survivor was filmed on the Samoan island of Upolu and featured 24 Australian castaways competing for 55 days in the Samoan jungle for a grand prize of A$500,000.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: In a world-first, this program has pitted 12 giants of Australian society against 12 everyday Aussies in order to create one epic battle: champions versus contenders.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: The game starts to become very real for the castaways. The reality of having to catch their own food and create a liveable shelter becomes top priority in camp.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: In the Champions camp a new leader steps forward and starts calling the shots, while over at The Contenders it's a case of the boys versus the girls.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Reeling after a shocking outcome in Tribal, one tribe is very unsettled and new targets start to come under fire.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: A castaway who has been struggling with the game becomes determined to stick with the fight. While one of the Contenders struggles with an injury so serious, it could spell the end of their game.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: From illness to dummy spits, time in isolation is starting to take its toll on some of the Castaways and it's causing unease in the camps.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: After a surprising tribal council result, some castaways realise they're on the outer and start to scramble to make alliances within their tribe.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: The twist in the previous game has one tribe torn and plotting new strategies to kick out one of the biggest competitors in the game.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: The game steps it up a notch when two castaways who have been on the edge of their team come face-to-face in front of their tribe.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: After losing at an endurance challenge for immunity, one team enters in what looks to be the fiercest Tribal Council yet.

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview: After 25 days on the island, the castaways have made the halfway point in the game, and their chance of becoming Sole Survivor is getting closer and more obtainable.

episodes.name: Episode 12
episodes.overview: After a massive shake-up in the game, both tribes are cautiously reforming plans and forging new alliances.

episodes.name: Episode 13
episodes.overview: As the game heats up with a merger, some islanders are starting to struggle, while others are just beginning to orchestrate their big moves. One of the program's biggest threats will be cut loose.

episodes.name: Episode 14
episodes.overview: It's auction time. The hungry castaways are given $500 each to enter into a new kind of battle where food is the hottest property in town.

episodes.name: Episode 15
episodes.overview: Mat and Robbie have faced off time and time again, but is it time to send one of them home?

episodes.name: Episode 16
episodes.overview: The end game is getting closer. Hold your breath! Contenders will rise and champions will fall. The big players make their move.

episodes.name: Episode 17
episodes.overview: The end game is getting closer and the scramble for survival more desperate, sparking the hunt for idols. Later, at a massive Tribal Council, one player's confidence just might cost them the game.

episodes.name: Episode 18
episodes.overview: After an unexpected result at Tribal Council, the Castaways' Camp is a hive of animosity and distrust. Hard truths come to the surface and split the opinions of the tribe.

episodes.name: Episode 19
episodes.overview: With only seven castaways that still remain, the game's power rests with one, and it's not who you think. What Monica is about to do next really shakes things up.

episodes.name: Episode 20
episodes.overview: With bitter grudges in play, victory at an immunity challenge has never been more important. At Tribal Council, accusations fly as some tribe members are accused of being carried through the game.

episodes.name: Episode 21
episodes.overview: As the game comes close to the end, the taste of victory is closer than ever. Trust between the castaways is at an all-time low and a bold move is made by a player to gain further power.

episodes.name: Episode 22
episodes.overview: As the pointy end of the game closes in on the remaining five castaways, one player seeks revenge after the previous tribal council.

episodes.name: Episode 23
episodes.overview: With only a few days left in the game, physical strength dwindling and emotions at an all-time high, the castaways are granted an opportunity for immunity, thus securing their place in the final three.

episodes.name: Episode 24
episodes.overview: After 50 testing days, the remaining three castaways can finally see and feel the eagerly anticipated finish line ahead of them, with one of the greatest battles for immunity in front of them.

episodes.name: Reunion Special
episodes.overview: The final two make their plea, with the jury to vote on who will be crowned the title of Sole Survivor and win $500,000. Then, all 24 castaways get together for an explosive and exciting reunion.

5.name: Champions vs. Contenders I
5.overview:
The fifth season of Australian Survivor, also known as Australian Survivor: Champions vs. Contenders.

The season featured 24 contestants divided into two tribes: "Champions", composed of twelve high-achievers who excelled in their fields, and "Contenders", composed of twelve everyday Australians.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: In the ultimate test of the human spirit, 12 everyday Aussies take on 12 Australian champions over 50 days to see who can outwit, outplay and outlast to become the sole 'survivor'.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Only a few days on the island, and alliances are already starting to form. It's still a team game as the rewards challenge requires a huge effort from all in order to take home some fishing equipment.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: After a loss at the Immunity Challenge, one tribe will contemplate a major betrayal in order to rid the game of one of its most powerful players.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: The contenders play hard in the challenges, desperate to prove they've got what it takes to win. Tensions are high at Tribal Council with one player taken down in an epic blindside and sent home.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Strategic gameplay is underway as one of the contestants finds an idol and needs to decide fast who can be trusted. Paranoia sets in at Tribal Council with confusion and panic taking over.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Paranoia starts to set in across both tribes with rumours of contestants having idols, but are they real or fake? At Tribal Council, the tribe are faced with some big questions around leadership.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: A massive twist in the game sees things shaken up for both the Contenders and the Champions. Old alliances will be broken, and those who were at the top of the game find themselves on the bottom.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Who is controlling the game? Will their antics soon be uncovered? Will they fall victim to their own success? Or are they still calling the shots?

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: In camp, plans start to unravel, leading to an epic Tribal Council no one saw coming that leaves everyone shocked.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: Tribe members have been given a wake up call, and it's clear to everyone that it's every man for himself in the game of Survivor.

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview: One Tribe considers a huge move in order to keep an alliance strong. But will they go through with it? At Tribal Council, there is a dramatic exit.

episodes.name: Episode 12
episodes.overview: With the first challenge involving heights and blindfolds and the second requiring all their strength, everyone is pushed to the edge - except one survivor who appears to be throwing the game.

episodes.name: Episode 13
episodes.overview: Things get a bit panicked around the camps with all survivors feeling their necks on the line, but an unexpected setback at the challenge will turn the whole game on its head.

episodes.name: Episode 14
episodes.overview: The first challenge consists of a series of temptations. What will the hungry survivors fall for? And one survivor makes sure that if they're going down, they're going down in flames.

episodes.name: Episode 15
episodes.overview: We are well and truly down to an individual game now and this time around, the prize is a brand-new car. What lengths will the survivors go to get their hands on the keys?

episodes.name: Episode 16
episodes.overview: The survivors enter one of the biggest Tribal Councils of the season as an unexpected move turns the game on its head.

episodes.name: Episode 17
episodes.overview: An unlikely duo battle it out in an endurance challenge. All sorts of names are being thrown up for the Tribal Council vote, but the name that keeps coming up the most is one you won't expect.

episodes.name: Episode 18
episodes.overview: The individual game gets desperate with several Survivors sneaking around camp searching for the idol that will save their game. Secrets aren't staying safe leading into a high-drama Tribal Council.

episodes.name: Episode 19
episodes.overview: Storms roll over camp and dampen all moods. As we inch closer towards the pointy end of things, old alliances are starting to crack as everyone starts to fight hard for their place in the game.

episodes.name: Episode 20
episodes.overview: When two of the biggest warriors in the game go head-to-head, a hard-fought battle ends in tears. It's a brutal Tribal Council where some hard truths are laid on the line.

episodes.name: Episode 21
episodes.overview: The survivors dive into some of the heaviest gameplay of the season. Loyalties fly out the window and old alliances are broken as each survivor tries desperately to keep their place in the tribe.

episodes.name: Episode 22
episodes.overview: No one is safe at this point in the game, leaving all contestants desperate to get their hands on the Immunity necklace to buy themselves another day in camp.

episodes.name: Episode 23
episodes.overview: With the end in sight, every move the contestants make could be the difference between making the final three or being voted out of the game.

episodes.name: Episode 24
episodes.overview: On the last day, the final two contestants head to their last Tribal Council where they have to convince the jury that they deserve the title of sole survivor.

6.name: Champions vs. Contenders II
6.overview:
The sixth season of Australian Survivor, also known as Australian Survivor: Champions vs. Contenders.

As with the previous season, the season features 24 contestants divided into two tribes: "Champions", composed of twelve high-achievers who excelled in their fields, and "Contenders", composed of twelve everyday Australians.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: The best competition on TV is bigger than ever. The biggest villains, game players and heroes, are seeking redemption and competing against each other in the first ever Australian Survivor: All Stars.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Proving it's game on, things heat up between tribe mates, with new alliances being formed and others being kept in the dark. An intense Tribal Council sees a much loved character say goodbye.

episodes.name: Episode 13
episodes.overview: With one tribe member knowing their name is on the parchment to be eliminated, a scramble ensues. Will friends suddenly become enemies?

episodes.name: Episode 14
episodes.overview: It's day 29 in Savusavu and the vibe among both tribes is that a merge is imminent.

episodes.name: Episode 15
episodes.overview: Still on a high from blindsiding another big player, some players are walking on air, while others are rethinking their rankings.

episodes.name: Episode 16
episodes.overview: As the last original member of the Little Rascals alliance, Shonee had to continue working her social game around Kalokalo, learning that she was born in the same area where Tarzan comes from.

episodes.name: Episode 17
episodes.overview: A frustrated Moana had to rebuild after being dragged to Exile Beach along with A.K. and Brooke, while Shonee found herself on her own against the Mokuta majority. Stunned at the thought of returning to Exile Beach this season, she continued to further her social connections in the Kalokalo tribe. David, being aware of Shonee's social prowess, felt adamant in sending her back to Exile, all while avoiding the likelihood of joining her with using his poor health as a crutch in potential challenges.

episodes.name: Episode 18
episodes.overview:
A.K. didn't believe Zach's story of volunteering for Exile, acknowledging it was probably David's manipulation at work. Jacqui was despondant by her alliance sending her to Exile Beach; she noticed that Zach's been groomed for David's endgame over other players, and that she needed to use her time on Exile to turn people against David. Shonee targeted Jacqui's frustrations to work her social game.

Kalokalo enjoyed a peaceful morning with just the 3 remaining players. Sharn felt she had to keep David in the game, but the information Tarzan brought to David the previous day made David's trust with Sharn falter, and the threat of the exiled players bonding loomed over his game.

episodes.name: Episode 19
episodes.overview: Jacqui's blindside of Zach left David feeling vulnerable and reconnecting with Tarzan as a potential shield. The blindside left the Vakama minority and Moana feeling more comfortable in exploiting Jacqui's confidence and David's vulnerability to their advantage, respectively.

episodes.name: Episode 20
episodes.overview: Sometimes the swing vote in Survivor is the most powerful position to be in. During Tribal Council, one tribe member is implored for their vote by both sides, giving them the power of the game.

episodes.name: Episode 21
episodes.overview: After missing out on the immunity challenge win, a hunt for an idol ensues and as always with Tribal Council, not all is as it seems and Jonathan has one last trick up his sleeve.

episodes.name: Episode 22
episodes.overview: With one tribe member on the bottom of the group, they know the only way to secure their place in the game is to win individual immunity.

episodes.name: Episode 23
episodes.overview: With the next immunity challenge deciding who will make the final three, it's more important than ever to be on your game, but for one castaway, island life is taking a toll on their body.

episodes.name: Episode 24
episodes.overview: The Grand Finale where a Sole Survivor All Star is crowned after 50 days of competing in Fiji.

7.name: All Stars
7.overview:
In Australian Survivor: All Stars, the game’s most iconic Champions and super fans, return for a slice of the scheming pie in the ultimate re-match.

Returning to a game they all think they’ve mastered, the players are in for a rude awakening. The challenges are harder, the alliances stronger and the blindsides more epic.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Cloncurry in north-west Queensland is where the ultimate battle between Brains and Brawn begins. As soon as the castaways hit the red dirt, it's every man for themselves to win the first reward challenge.

episodes.name: Episode 20
episodes.overview: Dani & Flick are on the bottom of the pack, but they are two strong physical & social threats who are here to fight. Will George’s kingdom crumble under the persuasive powers of the remaining Brawn?

episodes.name: Episode 21
episodes.overview: Dani concedes that the only way to get ahead in this game is to exploit some cracks in the majority alliance, but that would mean trusting someone who has betrayed her in the past.

episodes.name: Episode 22
episodes.overview: Day 44. The four former brains have formed an impenetrable alliance leaving Flick, the only remaining brawn, on the outer. Little do they know she's getting ready to shake things up!

episodes.name: Episode 23
episodes.overview: As we near the end of the competition, will the game's longest lasting power couple finally have to turn on each other?

episodes.name: Episode 24
episodes.overview: Who will outwit... outplay... and outlast the other to become the ultimate Sole Survivor in the final episode of Brains Vs. Brawn?

8.name: Brains vs. Brawn
8.overview: Australian Survivor sees 24 tough and tenacious people marooned on a tropical island with little more than the clothes on their backs and the drive to be the sole survivor.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Located in Far North Queensland, 24 castaways face off with their loved ones to see who has what it takes to be crowned Sole Survivor.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Battle lines are drawn with one castaway is on the outs with the Blue Tribe. Then, when an idol is found, someone at Tribal Council tries to flush it. Will they succeed?

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: A new day, a new Reward Challenge, with a trip to the coveted Survivor Shop. One person from the winning tribe is able to take someone from the other tribe along with them.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: When one member from the losing Tribe is invited to the winning Tribe's Reward Challenge treat of croissants and sweet things, it's a long overdue reunion for one cute pair.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: The gruelling barrel Immunity Challenge is back. Castaways must withstand the heat while holding their weight. In an epic battle, one person dials up hero mode and wins the challenge for their Tribe.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: In another epic Immunity Challenge, two Castaways push themselves to their limits, leading to potentially dire consequences for their Tribes. Then, One Castaway breaks ranks and warns a friend

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: It's Tribe Swap time! As the game heats up, the time has come for the Castaways to truly play their own game, even if it means turning on a loved one.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Last night's Tribal Council plays on the minds of quite a few Castaways. In true Tribe Swap fashion, not everything is rosy as strong personalities struggle to navigate a new environment.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: The game is well and truly underway with one Castaway deciding the time is right to start playing alliances off one another.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: It's another epic reward challenge, this time for a picnic with all the trimmings, and while the winning Tribe is ecstatic, one Castaway is nursing an injury.

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview: The game is well and truly underway, with one castaway deciding the time is right to start playing alliances off one another.

episodes.name: Episode 12
episodes.overview: It's no surprise that it's always the quiet ones you need to watch for, and tonight someone's game really begins to heat up.

episodes.name: Episode 13
episodes.overview: Another testing Immunity Challenge, with the last two standing being the most unexpected. With secrets exposed and alliances rocked, the vote at Tribal Council is a total surprise for one Castaway.

episodes.name: Episode 14
episodes.overview: In a puzzle making Immunity Challenge, a challenge beast is exposed. Will this place a huge target on their back and get them eliminated from the game?

episodes.name: Episode 15
episodes.overview: After winning everyone's favourite finger licking good reward, one of the Castaways snaffles an Idol clue for themselves, but has the lucky find been spotted by their alliance?

episodes.name: Episode 16
episodes.overview: It's all fun and games until an Idol comes between a couple of Castaways. After one of the toughest Immunity Challenges yet, could new alliances lead to a voting tug of war at Tribal Council?

episodes.name: Episode 17
episodes.overview: Backlash from the most devious move in Australian Survivor history hits camp. Desperate to win the Immunity Challenge, one Castaway is looking strong, but will they be able to hold out?

episodes.name: Episode 18
episodes.overview: Trying to get your Tribe to believe your story can make or break your game, as one Castaway tries to spell out the truth. Three Castaways are on the outer, and bond together over a shared experience.

episodes.name: Episode 19
episodes.overview: As castaways return to camp from Purgatory, alliances are seemingly reformed. A tribemate selflessly gives up their reward, and the game is flipped once more as Tribal Council sees an advantage played.

episodes.name: Episode 20
episodes.overview: Fallout from last night's Tribal Council divides the remaining tribemates. From playing in the middle to striking from the top, one Castaway proves they were merely biding their time to make big moves

episodes.name: Episode 21
episodes.overview: Reeling after the latest Tribal Council, the remaining Castaways take stock of what's occurred and where it leaves them in the game. A Reward Challenge side deal leaves some tribemates on the outer.

episodes.name: Episode 22
episodes.overview: A puzzle Immunity Challenge separates the muscles from the strategic, but will the result upset an alliance? At Tribal Council, nothing goes to plan as unwelcome surprises leave everyone on edge.

episodes.name: Episode 23
episodes.overview: The end is nigh as five Castaways are whittled down to four. At the Immunity Challenge, everyone digs deep but one tribemate pulls out all the stops, giving them a great shot at being Sole Survivor.

episodes.name: Episode 24
episodes.overview: After 47 days in the Queensland wilderness, it all comes down to this. An epic challenge weeds out the weak from the strong, and one castaway is crowned Sole Survivor, walking away with AU$500,000.

9.name: Blood vs Water
9.overview: Located in Far North Queensland, 24 castaways face off with their loved ones to see who has what it takes to be crowned Sole Survivor.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Returning players and new faces battle it out on the beaches of Samoa in Heroes v Villains. Who will outwit, outplay and outlast to become Sole Survivor and take out the half million dollar prize?

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: It's the mind game that will get you ahead, and our castaways will stop at nothing to make it through another night. Who will be sent to Tribal Council, and who will be plotting revenge?

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Following a heated Reward Challenge, a secret night mission causes one tribe to question one of their own. With another Tribal Council looming, players must think quickly in order to keep in the game.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Our Heroes and Villains go head-to-head in the ultimate Reward Challenge, and one tribe will be counting their lucky stars to avoid an unhinged Tribal Council.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: It's day 10 and unexpected alliances are formed. But it's not long before the cracks begin to show. As new alliances brew, tribes must work quickly and efficiently when facing a mega showdown at the all-important Immunity Challenge. Who will best navigate the twists and turns and be triumphant?

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: The Heroes and Villains are presented with a major prize of lasagne and photos from home up for grabs. Which tribe will dominate the Reward Challenge and possibly help create bonds stronger than ever?

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Survivor history will be made as the game is raised to a whole new level. And a jaw dropping Tribal Council leads to an all-out war, leaving one player's game, decimated.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: After the most explosive Tribal Council ever witnessed, one Tribe is in disarray. With alliances burnt to the ground, can anyone rise from the ashes?

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: A favourite brings a shocking twist that will flip the game on its head.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: 21 days into the game and the recent tribe swap is breeding fear and doubt amongst the new tribes.

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview: Last night's tribal council has revealed cracks amongst alliances. Which players will take advantage?

episodes.name: Episode 12
episodes.overview: The biggest blunder in Survivor history turns a player into public enemy number one. With no alliances left do they have any chance of survival?

episodes.name: Episode 13
episodes.overview: It's day 26 and the OG members of one tribe are on a high with the return of a much-loved ally.

episodes.name: Episode 14
episodes.overview: The greatest end game is about to be unleashed. Can alliances reunite, as enemies collide?

episodes.name: Episode 15
episodes.overview: A powerful force has taken over the game. But can old enemies be trusted? Will vengeance and betrayal blow the game apart?

episodes.name: Episode 16
episodes.overview: The Vigilantes have taken over. Can the OG Heroes hang on for dear life?

episodes.name: Episode 17
episodes.overview: With the end in sight, the remaining castaways are desperate to do anything to survive. Will jealousy cost one castaway the game, or can they keep level-headed enough to make it through another night?

episodes.name: Episode 18
episodes.overview: With numbers dwindling, it's anyone's game to take out the title of Sole Survivor. When two castaways put their best moves forward, will their plan to win over the alliance work?

episodes.name: Episode 19
episodes.overview: A Reward Challenge where the winner gets an overnight stay and delicious feast in the Survivor Spa has everyone salivating! Then, grab the popcorn, as it all goes down at an intense Tribal Council?

episodes.name: Episode 20
episodes.overview: Which remaining castaway will push their willpower to the limit to win tonight's Immunity Challenge? Tribal Council then sees the game flipped on its head once more as desperation sets in.

episodes.name: Episode 21
episodes.overview: The end is in sight, but it will require damage control, betrayal of allies and master manipulation for one of the castaways to navigate the muddy waters of the game to become Sole Survivor.

episodes.name: Episode 22
episodes.overview: We've reached the top five on Australia Survivor: Heroes V Villains and it's crunch time. Desperate to win the Immunity Challenge, one castaway is looking strong, but can they hold out?

episodes.name: Episode 23
episodes.overview: Betrayal is central to some players' strategy, driving the remaining castaways' paranoia to maximum as they strive to become the Sole Survivor, and this episode's twist will send tensions through the roof.

episodes.name: Episode 24
episodes.overview: The final Tribal Council has arrived. Who has the most complete resume and convincing case to be crowned the winner and take home the $500k prize that goes with it?

10.name: Heroes vs. Villains
10.overview: In the game of Australian Survivor, who does it better? A hero or a villain? This season, we are back to where it all began. Samoa. Where the beautiful beaches will see heroes and villains battle it out in gruelling challenges to come out on top. Hosted by Jonathan LaPaglia, the eighth season of Australian Survivor is an unrelenting test of courage, endurance and strength that will push people to their limits and beyond.

episodes.name: We've All Seen This Movie
episodes.overview: With 24 brand new players back on the beaches of Samoa, who will outwit, outplay, and outlast the others to take home the half million-dollar prize?

episodes.name: The Invisible Hand
episodes.overview: A clever strategy partnership, 'The Invisible Hand' tries to control the game. But can these two tribe mates stay out of the firing line?

episodes.name: The Cuddle Club
episodes.overview: The Rebels are in high spirits and the cuddle club have big plans to strengthen their tribe. But can they pull it off?

episodes.name: B Is for Blindside
episodes.overview: The Titans wake up in high spirits, but nothing is quite as it seems when a new discovery raises suspicions.

episodes.name: Where Angels Fear to Tread
episodes.overview: The aftermath of Tribal Council hits home as a strong alliance is left untethered. Can an uncovered mystery give rise to a new power? Or will is cause more friction than ever before?

episodes.name: The Saboteur
episodes.overview: Both tribes deal with the aftermath of Tribal Council and a hurricane of a different sort, comes to Survivor beach. Strategies are questioned. Who will be going home tonight?

episodes.name: Get, Or Get Got
episodes.overview: With the easy vote out of the way, each tribe begins to turn on one another and a major milestone of the game gets in the way of their plans.

episodes.name: The Divorce
episodes.overview: Following an epic blindside, one tribe is divided and another is out for revenge. And after a chaotic scramble, where no one believes anyone, anything can happen at Tribal Council.

episodes.name: Excited for the Actions
episodes.overview: Someone is left groveling for survival. Meanwhile, a mouth-watering reward is up for grabs, but can it be enough to strengthen tribe mate suspicions?

episodes.name: Bad Hair Day
episodes.overview: Is it worth taking a chance with a new alliance or should you trust someone again? Anything can happen at Tribal Council?

episodes.name: It's Not Sarong, It's So Right
episodes.overview: The aftermath of last night's Tribal Council lingers and revenge is on the cards. An endurance challenge could see a rising star emerge and Tribal Council isn't quite as it seems.

episodes.name: To Infinity and Beyond
episodes.overview: A second chance is up for grabs, and a Reward twist changes the power dynamics of the two dominant alliances. Who will be going home tonight?

episodes.name: Revenge Is a Dish Best Served Russian
episodes.overview: An alliance still reeling from an earlier vote, leads to an all-out war. But their plan to avenge their friend's blindside leads to outbursts and twists at Tribal Council.

episodes.name: A Line in the Sand
episodes.overview: Divided more than ever after the previous tribal, a feud continues to rampage through the tribe tearing alliances apart. Who will be going home tonight?

episodes.name: Master and Apprentice
episodes.overview: Newly formed alliances are tested, and an epic Reward is up for grabs that could change everything. Who will be going home tonight?

episodes.name: Episode 16
episodes.overview: Eleven contestants remain and an opportunity to take back control of the game is on someone's mind. Where will the votes fall tonight and who will become the first jury member?

episodes.name: Episode 17
episodes.overview: As a powerful new alliance sends ripples through the camp, who will stay loyal to friends and alliances, and who will jump ship?

episodes.name: Episode 18
episodes.overview: A risky advantage is in play but will an alliance trust enough to help pull it off, or will it all end in failure?

episodes.name: Episode 19
episodes.overview: A boy's alliance starts to form, and someone is on a mission to take out a big player. Eight are left. Who will be going home tonight?

episodes.name: Episode 20
episodes.overview: For one, paranoia takes hold for the first time and wounded egos collide after an explosive Tribal Council. Everyone's hungry to make big moves and impress the Jury

episodes.name: Episode 21
episodes.overview: With only five days left, loyalties are tested and powers shift. With only six Survivors left, who will be going home tonight?

episodes.name: Episode 22
episodes.overview: Someone's in the firing line and another must make an impossible choice. With only a few days left of the game, who will be going home tonight?

episodes.name: Episode 23
episodes.overview: The final four are left and tensions are on the rise as deals are exposed. An all-out war is on the cards. Who will be safe from the vote tonight?

episodes.name: Episode 24
episodes.overview: After 45 days of battling it out in Samoa, the final three will be pushed to their limits. Who will be crowned Sole Survivor in Titans vs Rebels?

11.name: Titans v Rebels
11.overview:
In this season, twenty-four contestants were stranded in Samoa and divided into two tribes of Titans and Rebels.

The season was filmed in Upolu, Samoa, the same location of the previous season.
